cho_description:
Panels from the stone sarcophagus of Menna, the mayor of Nennesut (Herakleopolis). 
Ancient Egyptian New Kingdom, late 18th - early 19th Dynasty, ca. 1323-1213 B.C.
Panels depict two of the four sons of Horus.  On the left is Imsety and the right is Duamutef.
San Antonio Museum of Art.
Created in Agisoft Photoscan from 71, 18MP photos using a Canon EOS Rebel T3.
cho_title: Panels from the Sarcophagus of Menna
